Reasoning: The paper proposes a neural network architecture that can handle multiple modalities (such as image, text, and video) and multiple tasks (such as part-of-speech tagging, image captioning, visual question answering, and video activity recognition) simultaneously. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with tasks that involve both visual and textual information.
